Example: scaleX(2) doubles the width of the element.

1. scaleY(value)
   Description: Stretches or shrinks an element vertically along the Y-axis.
   Example: scaleY(2) doubles the height of the element.

2. scale(x, y)
   Description: Scales an element on both X and Y axes.
   Example: scale(1.5, 1.5) increases both width and height by 1.5 times.

3. translateX(value)
   Description: Moves an element horizontally by the specified value.
   Example: translateX(2em) moves the element 2em to the right.

4. translateY(value)
   Description: Moves an element vertically by the specified value.
   Example: translateY(2em) moves the element 2em downward.

5. translate(x, y)
   Description: Moves an element both horizontally (X-axis) and vertically (Y-axis).
   Example: translate(2em, 2em) moves it 2em right and 2em down.

6. matrix(a, b, c, d, e, f)
   Description: Applies a 2D transformation using six values to manipulate position, scaling, rotation, or skew.
   Example: matrix(1, -1, 0, 1, 0, 0) flips the element vertically.

7. rotate(angle)
   Description: Rotates an element around the Z-axis.
   Example: rotate(270deg) rotates the element 270 degrees clockwise.

8. skew(angleX, angleY)
   Description: Skews (tilts) an element on both the X and Y axes.
   Example: skew(30deg, 20deg) tilts it by 30 degrees horizontally and 20 degrees vertically.

9. skewX(angle)
   Description: Skews an element only on the X-axis.
   Example: skewX(30deg) tilts it 30 degrees horizontally.

10. skewY(angle)
    Description: Skews an element only on the Y-axis.
    Example: skewY(30deg) tilts it 30 degrees vertically.

11. matrix3d()
    Description: Applies a 3D transformation using 16 values to manipulate position, rotation, or scaling in 3D space.
    Example: Complex 3D transformations like perspective or rotation.

12. translate3d(x, y, z)
    Description: Moves an element along the X, Y, and Z axes.
    Example: translate3d(1px, 1px, 50px) moves the element deeper into the screen (Z-axis) while moving right and down slightly.

13. rotateY(angle)
    Description: Rotates an element around the Y-axis (3D effect).
    Example: rotateY(45deg) creates a horizontal flip effect at 45 degrees.

14. rotateX(angle)
    Description: Rotates an element around the X-axis (3D effect).
    Example: rotateX(45deg) creates a vertical flip effect at 45 degrees.

15. translateZ(value)
    Description: Moves an element along the Z-axis (depth).
    Example: translateZ(50px) pushes the element 50px closer or farther away.

16. perspective(value)
    Description: Defines the perspective from which all child elements are viewed.
    Example: perspective(500px) sets the perspective to 500px.